SIMPLE: crunch
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crunch
<hw>Crunch</hw> <pr>(kr⟦ucr⟧nch)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Crunched</conjf>
<pr>(kr⟦ucr⟧ncht)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Crunching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Prob. of imitative origin; or
cf. D. <ets>schransen</ets> to eat heartily, or E.
<ets>scrunch</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To chew with force and
noise; to craunch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And their white tusks <qex>crunched</qex> o'er the whiter
skull.</q> <rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To grind or press with violence and noise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ship <qex>crunched</qex> through the ice.</q>
<rj><qau>Kane.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To emit a grinding or craunching noise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>crunching</qex> and ratting of the loose stones.</q>
<rj><qau>H. James.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crunch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Crunch
<hw>Crunch</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To crush with the teeth; to chew
with a grinding noise; to craunch; <as>as, to <ex>crunch</ex> a
biscuit</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crunkle</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Crunk</ent>⟦br⟧
